  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-04 01:06 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] 8fcc closes BTC short, but consensus turns bearish\n\n**Task:** Run fresh copy-intel and decide whether the prior maximum defensive trigger clears after `anon-0x8fcc` exits its BTC short.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Ran `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/copy-intel-tracker.py`.\n- Fresh leaderboard consensus shifted from prior **BTC 5L/4S bullish** to **BTC 3L/5S bearish**.\n- `anon-0x8fcc` closed BTC entirely, removing the prior single-wallet hard trigger.\n- Bearish offsets appeared immediately: `anon-0xf5d8` BTC **LONG\u2192SHORT** (~$178.9k), `anon-0xff4c` BTC **LONG\u2192SHORT** (~$4.2k), and `beatmaker1@proton.me` BTC **LONG\u2192SHORT** (~$384.5k).\n- `anon-0xc926` flipped BTC **SHORT\u2192LONG**, but the broader count stayed bearish.\n- Current tracked exposure: BTC **3L/$9.77M vs 5S/$8.52M**, net **+$1.25M**; ETH **3L/$1.70M vs 5S/$33.24M**, net **-$31.54M**; SOL **3L/$42.7k vs 5S/$9.56M**, net **-$9.52M**; HYPE **5L/$1.76M vs 4S/$12.05M**, net **-$10.28M**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-8fcc-closes-but-btc-consensus-bearish-2026-05-04-0106.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The `8fcc` close is real risk easing, but it did not produce a copy-intel green light. BTC net is only slightly positive and still far below the **+$10M** hard-clear threshold, while the trader count flipped bearish and ETH/SOL/HYPE remain deeply short by notional.\n\n**Decision:** Remove the specific `8fcc` hard trigger, but keep P1 **defensive**. Do not enable PM/HL expansion from copy intel yet. Require BTC net **>$10M**, BTC count neutral/bullish, and easing ETH/SOL/HYPE short clusters before downgrading to risk-on/watch.\n\n**Next:** Track whether the new smaller BTC shorts persist or quickly flip back. If BTC net stays positive while count remains bearish, build a count-vs-notional rule so one large BTC long cannot mask broad short consensus.\n\n## 2026-05-04 01:03 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Stable mixed RANGE, extreme compression; P1 hard defensive\n\n**Task:** Refresh P4 alpha after risk-easing mixed-transition, checking whether compression cools below 1.5 or remains extreme while P1 stays hard defensive.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P4**.\n- Ran fresh `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/alpha-signal-update.sh`.\n- Current alpha timestamp: **2026-05-04T01:02:45.358171+00:00**.\n- BTC price **$78,444.28**, 24h **+0.204%**; Fear & Greed **40 Fear**.\n- Top-level schema drift persists: `regime_state` is raw **RANGE** object while top-level `posture` and `pm_risk` are **null**.\n- Nested context: classifier **mixed_transition**, stance **reduced**, nested PM risk **low**, transition posture **stable**, transition label **unchanged_distinct_state**.\n- BTC microstructure: realized vol 1h **0.2168%**, avg range last 6h **0.5887%**, compression **2.3938**, 6h trend **-0.4013%**, ",
